{"questionId":"e3fe84c7-8083-48b8-863b-841355113ba0_21","correctAnswer":"A","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Use the factored form","content":"Since the parabola has roots $8$ and $-2$, $f(x)=a(x-8)(x-(-2))$ for integer $a>1$."},{"title":"Expand to find $a+b$","content":"Expanding gives $f(x)=ax^2-a(8+(-2))x+a(8)(-2)$, so $b=-a(6)$ and $$a+b=a(1-(6))=-5a.$$"},{"title":"Pick a valid $a$","content":"With $a=2$ (integer $>1$), $a+b=-5\\cdot2=-10$. The answer is <strong>A</strong>."}]}